  "text": "Our data structure can also be understood as a type of sketching data structure . These are data structures that can answer certain questions about the data they store extremely efficiently, at the price of an occasional error. Examples of sketching data structures are Bloom filters [CITATION_1] , count-min sketch [CITATION_2] and the LFN data structure [CITATION_3] . . p Δ However, by trading off a small resolution, they can achieve higher performance. In particular, because many real world applications do not require priority queues to support infinite resolution spaces, in many of these cases MR-PQs can be used to achieve greater performance at no cost, as we will show.",
